“I’ve had acne-prone skin my entire adult life, and I’ve gone through a real journey to try and learn and manage my skin.” Supermodel and entrepreneur #RosieHuntingtonWhiteley has created her own make-up and skincare line @RoseInc, incorporating essentials from a concealer and a cream blush to an exfoliating toner, and it launches on 27 August. Watch as she shows you how she creates her signature rosy glow using some of her favourite products. 

Directed by @In.Between.Studios.

Star of the smash hit @NetflixUK show ‘Money Heist’, #UrsulaCorbero sits down in Madrid to empty her bag and reveal the unique stories behind every item. From a Tamagotchi she was given at a photoshoot, to the good luck charm her father-in-law – Argentinian actor Ricardo Darín – gave her when they first met, watch as she shows Vogue what’s inside her bag.

Directed by @Modernetta, produced by @Emece_________ and @ZukiElliott, and edited by @Almu_Molero.

In the latest #MakeUpMasters episode with #BritishVogue, watch as the pair take on the classic Hollywood look using the new make-up line from @Valentino.Beauty. You’ll be achieving winged eyeliner like #SophiaLoren in no time.

node.text:
An artist, a businesswoman, a one-woman powerhouse, @Beyonce has been breaking new ground since the start of her career – and she’s showing no signs of slowing down. On her 40th birthday, revisit her interview from the December 2020 issue of #BritishVogue, in which she talks to @Edward_Enninful about racial and social justice movements, her personal legacy, and why she finally gave herself permission to “focus on my joy”.

#Beyonce photographed by @InternetBby and styled by @Edward_Enninful with hair by @JawaraW and colourists @Rachel_Bodt and @ShirleyGHauteHair, make-up by @FrancescaTolot, nails by @OhMyNailsNYC, set design by @StefanBeckman and lighting direction by @_Wordie. With thanks to Beyoncé’s personal stylist @ZerinaAkers, her tailor #TimWhite and publicist @YvetteNoelSchure; Parkwood Entertainment creative director @KwasiFordjour and creative producer @LaurenLaLaBaker; Satellite414 founder @CarlitoF8; @TravisKiewel and @RobFamous for @ThatOneProduction; and Vogue entertainment director-at-large @JillDemling.

node.text: #DakotaJohnson in all her @Gucci glory is back on the red carpet for the #VeniceFilmFestival. Appearing in Italy for the premiere of ‘The Lost Daughter’ starring #OliviaColeman, #PaulMescal and directed by #MaggieGyllenhaal, the actor wore a dazzling sheer crystal-fringed dress, with her signature dreamlike mermaid waves to complete the look. Click the link in bio for more on her roaring twenties glamour.

The #VeniceFilmFestival is in full swing, and with it a flurry of glittering cocktail receptions and intimate soirées. Few, however, have been as star-studded as @Cartier’s dinner, hosted on 2 September by the storied jewellery house’s CEO Cyrille Vigneron at the spectacular Palazzo Giustiniani alle Zattere. #BritishVogue’s @Edward_Enninful was in attendance alongside screen regulars #RamiMalek, #IsabelleHuppert, and Hollywood super siblings #JakeGyllenhaal and #MaggieGyllenhaal. Click the link in bio to see inside the event.

Photographed by @GregWilliamsPhotography.

node.text:
Over the course of his stellar career, the legendary photographer #PeterLindbergh worked with some of the most famous models and actresses in the world. Famously unretouched and naturally lit, his images of the most glamorous A-listers were often stripped-back, cinematic portraits of unfiltered beauty. To honour Peter Lindbergh on the anniversary of his death, look back at 16 of his most exquisite photographs for #BritishVogue through the decades, at the link in bio.

#CindyCrawford photographed by Peter Lindbergh, with hair by @JulienDys and make-up by @Stephane_Marais_Officiali for the February 1989 issue of British Vogue.

node.text: A 1am photoshoot is not exactly standard, but September cover star #GemmaChan took it all in her stride. The actor has shared some behind-the-scenes snaps from the two chilly London nights she spent with the #BritishVogue team on the banks of the Thames, prepping for her sunrise shoot. Click the link in bio to read her interview in full, as she discusses reentering the @Marvel Universe, her efforts to tackle anti-Asian hate, representation in Hollywood, and her old friends #HarryStyles and #RichardMadden.

node.text: For #PenelopeCruz, no red-carpet look is complete without @ChanelOfficial. The Oscar-winning actor opened the 78th #VeniceFilmFestival with Pedro Almodóvar’s film ‘Parallel Mothers’, wearing a black and white gown from the maison’s AW21 haute couture collection, which took some 300 hours to make.
